                        Moreover, if the orbit of <m>\gamma_i</m> is <m>O</m>, then <m>\gamma_i</m> and <m>\sigma</m> act the same on <m>O</m> and <m>\gamma_i</m> fixes <m>\{1, \dots, n\} \setminus O</m>. 
                        It follows that <m>\gamma_i = \tau_O</m>.
