                    <li>
                      <p>
                        It suffices to prove this for a single cycle and, by symmetry, for the cycle <m>(1 \, 2 \, \cdots \, p)</m>. 
                        The equation <me>(1 \, 2 \, \cdots \, p) =  (1 \, 2) (2 \, 3) \cdots ((p-2) \, (p-1)) ((p-1) \, p)</me> is seen to hold by direct calculation.
